<p>to provide amusement for troops when in rest. They were really splendid &amp; we enjoyed the show immensely &ndash; Les returned our call last night and came over with young Varley, also in the 45th Battalion.</p>
<p>Today is Sunday and for a change it is a day of rest with us. Church parade this morning, and nothing to do this afternoon except amuse ourselves &ndash;</p>
<p>Fergusson &amp; Tait, two of my officers have gone into Amiens, the rest of us are giving our attention to a football match the boys of the Battery have arranged. It is a treat to get out of the mud on to some clean country where</p>
